SIMPLE: skittish
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Skittish
<hw>Skit"tish</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Skit</er>,
<pos>v. t.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Easily frightened; timorous;
shy; untrustworthy; <as>as, a <ex>skittish</ex> colt</as>.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧A restiff, <xex>skittish</xex> jade.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>L'Estrange.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Wanton; restive; freakish; volatile; changeable;
fickle.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Skittish</xex> Fortune's hall.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Skit"tish*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Skit"tish*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Skittle</ent>⟦br⟧
